Legislative History of Laws

For legislative history of D.C. Law 10-236, see Historical and Statutory Notes following § 2-1207.02.

Miscellaneous Notes

Expiration of Law 10-236: Section 6(b) of D.C. Law 10-236 provided that the act shall expire 3 years after having taken effect. D.C. Law 10-236, which added §§ 1-2261 to 1-2263 [§§ 2-1213.01 to 2-1213.03, 2001 Ed.], became effective on March 21, 1995.
